1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:29,510 --> 00:01:35,200
[Romance on the Farm]

3
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:37,930
[Episode 6]

4
00:01:38,289 --> 00:01:38,979
Youheng.

5
00:02:01,020 --> 00:02:03,220
He is indeed a member of the Lian family.

6
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,509
There are too many crops to tend to as a farmer.

7
00:02:09,509 --> 00:02:10,350
Constable.

8
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:11,860
It's normal that you've never met him

9
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:12,720
in the village.

10
00:02:13,350 --> 00:02:15,480
Although we shouldn't take things lightly,

11
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,150
if

12
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:17,550
you just randomly arrest someone

13
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:19,260
and send him back to the magistrate office,

14
00:02:19,260 --> 00:02:21,150
not only will you be blamed by the magistrate,

15
00:02:21,150 --> 00:02:22,750
but you'll also get caught up

16
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:25,430
such that there'll be no time to search for the real culprit.

17
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:26,270
Sirs.

18
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,060
Don't waste any more time

19
00:02:28,060 --> 00:02:28,720
on a farmer.

20
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:32,970
Constable Liu.

21
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:34,590
Even Youheng said so.

22
00:02:35,579 --> 00:02:36,579
What do you think?

23
00:02:47,660 --> 00:02:48,100
Go on.

24
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:56,720
Wang Youheng.

25
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,800
Why are you helping me?

26
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:04,500
I'm not helping you.

27
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:06,710
I just don't want

28
00:03:06,710 --> 00:03:08,640
to add trouble to Man'er's family.

29
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:10,540
As I said,

30
00:03:11,380 --> 00:03:12,870
once you're done with your affairs,

31
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,600
you should leave immediately.

32
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:15,700
Go.

33
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:35,660
Xiu'er.

34
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:38,329
We don't have to be angry with Man'er.

35
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:40,160
Am I mad at her?

36
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:41,880
I'm angry with Father.

37
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,130
So many people are watching.

38
00:03:44,670 --> 00:03:45,540
Not only did he scold me,

39
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:46,730
but he also hit me.

40
00:03:47,780 --> 00:03:48,620
That's because

41
00:03:48,620 --> 00:03:51,100
Lian Man'er tried to sow discord between Father and you.

42
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,380
Who knows if she isn't

43
00:03:53,010 --> 00:03:55,140
making up stories about you behind your back?

44
00:03:55,140 --> 00:03:55,829
Otherwise,

45
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,220
why would Father get so mad

46
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:59,060
with just those few words from you?

47
00:03:59,060 --> 00:03:59,590
Yes.

48
00:04:02,260 --> 00:04:04,270
But you're still family after all.

49
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,580
No matter how bad she is,

50
00:04:06,940 --> 00:04:07,970
you shouldn't

51
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:09,020
take it to heart.

52
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:10,720
Hua'er.

53
00:04:11,500 --> 00:04:12,430
What should I do?

54
00:04:15,010 --> 00:04:16,610
It's between you and Man'er.

55
00:04:17,089 --> 00:04:18,550
I shouldn't talk too much.

56
00:04:18,709 --> 00:04:19,269
Hua'er.

57
00:04:19,779 --> 00:04:21,440
Lian Man'er is such a bad girl.

58
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:23,500
Why do you still care so much for her?

59
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,030
Help me think of a solution.

60
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:31,560
F-Fine.

61
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,870
If I think of a good solution,

62
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,110
I'll tell you.

63
00:04:37,020 --> 00:04:38,620
You treat me the best indeed.

64
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:57,380
Father.

65
00:04:57,909 --> 00:04:58,700
Why did you call all of us here

66
00:04:58,700 --> 00:05:00,580
so early in the morning?

67
00:05:00,780 --> 00:05:02,980
Aren't we going to the fields in a while?

68
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:07,870
I called you here before heading to the fields

69
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,670
because I have something important

70
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:11,530
to discuss with the whole family.

71
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:13,580
I was planning

72
00:05:14,230 --> 00:05:15,830
to talk about it in a few days.

73
00:05:16,230 --> 00:05:18,030
But Shouren and his family

74
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:20,830
will be going back to town after the autumn harvest.

75
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:22,840
After thinking about it,

76
00:05:24,020 --> 00:05:26,270
I thought it'd be better to talk about this

77
00:05:26,270 --> 00:05:27,530
when everyone is here.

78
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,420
About this,

79
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,280
Shouren and I

80
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:37,090
have thought about it.

81
00:05:38,790 --> 00:05:39,460
I know

82
00:05:40,409 --> 00:05:41,220
that San'er

83
00:05:41,540 --> 00:05:42,930
is a filial son.

84
00:05:43,180 --> 00:05:45,450
I guess he wouldn't object either.

85
00:05:46,580 --> 00:05:47,110
Well.

86
00:05:48,490 --> 00:05:49,360
Hua'er

87
00:05:50,810 --> 00:05:52,380
is getting married soon.

88
00:05:53,830 --> 00:05:55,260
After getting married,

89
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:57,840
Shouren

90
00:05:58,390 --> 00:06:01,060
will have no children to take care of him.

91
00:06:04,380 --> 00:06:05,380
Zhang,

92
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:08,030
If this baby is a boy,

93
00:06:10,050 --> 00:06:11,850
you should let Shouren adopt it.

94
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:26,120
Father.

95
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:27,550
San'er.

96
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:29,230
You're still young.

97
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:31,100
You can have more children in the future.

98
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,300
From now on,

99
00:06:32,740 --> 00:06:34,790
this child will study and read with Shouren

100
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:35,970
and make achievements.

101
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:38,659
It's better than being a farmer at home.

102
00:06:40,470 --> 00:06:42,070
Then, a hundred years later,

103
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:43,180
Shouren

104
00:06:43,790 --> 00:06:44,370
will also have

105
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:46,630
someone to carry his coffin and bury him.

106
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,720
All right then.

107
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:00,590
It's a deal.

108
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:02,430
Grandpa.

109
00:07:07,150 --> 00:07:09,020
Since the whole family is here to discuss,

110
00:07:09,020 --> 00:07:10,350
I have a few words to say.

111
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:17,990
Go ahead.

112
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:22,650
Regardless of whether Eight is a boy or a girl,

113
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:24,380
Uncle Shouren cannot adopt it.

114
00:07:27,310 --> 00:07:29,570
Because we want to split from the family.

115
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:32,250
Split from the family?

116
00:07:33,090 --> 00:07:34,150
You heard it right.

117
00:07:34,650 --> 00:07:36,710
We're going to split from the family.

118
00:07:37,380 --> 00:07:38,380
I don't have a good son

119
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:39,960
or a good daughter-in-law.

120
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,200
How dare you split from your family?

121
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:44,830
Just take me to the mountain

122
00:07:45,020 --> 00:07:46,330
and bury me.

123
00:07:46,909 --> 00:07:47,370
Bury...

124
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:48,720
Mother.

125
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,280
Father... Father is angry.

126
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:50,680
Hurry.

127
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:00,780
San'er.

128
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:02,670
I know

129
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:04,630
that you don't talk about it,

130
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:05,990
but you're still

131
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:07,710
bothered by

132
00:08:07,730 --> 00:08:09,860
what happened to Man'er the last time.

133
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:12,820
But making mistakes

134
00:08:13,410 --> 00:08:15,210
is inevitable

135
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:17,080
for everyone.

136
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:18,890
Man'er.

137
00:08:19,580 --> 00:08:20,340
You're still young.

138
00:08:20,340 --> 00:08:21,530
There are many things you don't understand.

139
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:23,010
In this house,

140
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:26,160
other than the biological parents and children,

141
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,520
everyone's biological brothers.

142
00:08:27,520 --> 00:08:28,950
He broke the bones,

143
00:08:28,990 --> 00:08:30,950
the tendons weren't hurt.

144
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:33,679
No matter who did something wrong,

145
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:36,110
we have to be tolerant, right?

146
00:08:37,980 --> 00:08:39,350
We're a family.

147
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:41,980
If you think it through,

148
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:44,710
we have to work together.

149
00:08:45,710 --> 00:08:47,460
Once we split up,

150
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,140
then...

151
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:52,160
the familial bonds will be broken.

152
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:55,230
Grandpa, how did you

153
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:56,720
make such a cliched theory

154
00:08:57,170 --> 00:08:58,570
sound so grand?

155
00:08:59,060 --> 00:08:59,980
What did you say?

156
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:00,650
I said

157
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:04,290
that just because my parents are easy-going,

158
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:06,110
you naturally think that

159
00:09:06,300 --> 00:09:07,580
they can be wronged.

160
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:08,990
Man'er.

161
00:09:09,310 --> 00:09:09,830
Mother.

162
00:09:10,650 --> 00:09:11,430
Stop it.

163
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:14,280
Mother.

164
00:09:15,740 --> 00:09:16,870
Just now, Grandpa said so much

165
00:09:16,870 --> 00:09:17,480
about the logic

166
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,950
of familial relationships.

167
00:09:18,950 --> 00:09:20,340
But before, when Uncle Shouren

168
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:21,150
sold my life

169
00:09:21,180 --> 00:09:23,020
for a piece of broken jade pendant,

170
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,620
did he consider our kinship?

171
00:09:25,780 --> 00:09:26,470
Now,

172
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:29,010
they're eyeing the baby in your womb.

173
00:09:30,110 --> 00:09:31,510
If we don't hurry and split from the family,

174
00:09:31,510 --> 00:09:33,020
they'll bleed us dry.

175
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:38,990
This girl has a sharp tongue.

176
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:41,050
San'er.

177
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:45,000
Is this what you want to do too?

178
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:49,440
Do you really want to be separated from your parents?

179
00:09:54,350 --> 00:09:54,950
Father...

180
00:10:01,530 --> 00:10:02,520
I get it now.

181
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,190
Shouxin's family

182
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:24,920
wants to split from the family.

183
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,300
As brothers and sisters-in-law,

184
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:31,470
you should reflect on yourselves.

185
00:10:32,690 --> 00:10:34,810
You're going to be an official.

186
00:10:34,980 --> 00:10:36,740
After you become successful,

187
00:10:36,870 --> 00:10:38,970
you mustn't forget Shouxin's family

188
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:41,470
and support them in everything.

189
00:10:41,510 --> 00:10:42,580
Let them enjoy a comfortable life

190
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,320
along with you.

191
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:45,820
Remember that.

192
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:47,160
Father.

193
00:10:47,430 --> 00:10:48,630
I realize my mistake.

194
00:10:48,950 --> 00:10:50,880
Before, I was in a befuddled state.

195
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:53,400
From now on, I'll treat Shouxin

196
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,220
and Sister-in-law well.

197
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:56,820
Fine.

198
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,230
As I said,

199
00:11:02,220 --> 00:11:04,450
brothers

200
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,700
do not bear grudges.

201
00:11:07,430 --> 00:11:08,690
From now on, you need to

202
00:11:08,990 --> 00:11:10,820
be respectful and compromising with each other

203
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:12,350
like you used to.

204
00:11:12,830 --> 00:11:13,710
Got it?

205
00:11:14,930 --> 00:11:16,340
Yes, Grandpa.

206
00:11:16,930 --> 00:11:17,660
Yes.

207
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:24,580
San'er.

208
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:31,510
Your elder brother's family realized their mistake.

209
00:11:35,710 --> 00:11:36,170
Father.

210
00:11:37,850 --> 00:11:38,910
I'll listen to you.

211
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:42,620
No!

212
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:47,080
Did your parents say anything?

213
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:47,940
I said no!

214
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:49,670
You have no say in this. Shut up!

215
00:11:50,580 --> 00:11:51,650
Mother!

216
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:52,750
My Lord.

217
00:11:54,070 --> 00:11:54,570
Mother.

218
00:11:54,700 --> 00:11:55,500
What's wrong?

219
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:57,190
Go get a doctor now.

220
00:11:57,220 --> 00:11:57,580
Mother.

221
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:58,100
Go.

222
00:11:58,420 --> 00:11:58,820
Go.

223
00:11:58,990 --> 00:11:59,830
Hurry up.

224
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,700
Mother! Mother!

225
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,520
She has insufficient energy and blood

226
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:20,320
and the fetus's vital signs are a little unstable.

227
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:22,010
But there's no major problem.

228
00:12:22,470 --> 00:12:24,180
She just needs to rest.

229
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:26,990
Here.

230
00:12:29,220 --> 00:12:29,990
Seven.

231
00:12:32,580 --> 00:12:34,580
I'm glad you're fine. You scared me.

232
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:37,070
Look.

233
00:12:37,510 --> 00:12:38,820
The shoes Mother sewed for Eight

234
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:39,700
are finished.

235
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:41,550
Don't look at the shoes.

236
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,560
Take a good rest first.

237
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:52,960
I go to the temple every day

238
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,590
and pray to Buddha.

239
00:12:54,870 --> 00:12:56,780
Every day, my heart and liver are already bitter

240
00:12:56,780 --> 00:13:00,480
from taking medicine.

241
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:03,270
But you actually secretly

242
00:13:03,270 --> 00:13:04,780
discussed with Father

243
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:07,390
about adopting

244
00:13:07,430 --> 00:13:09,220
San'er's child.

245
00:13:12,110 --> 00:13:13,370
It's been so many years

246
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,440
and we haven't had any success.

247
00:13:16,210 --> 00:13:17,960
Father was just anxious.

248
00:13:19,470 --> 00:13:21,460
I think you're the one that's anxious.

249
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:22,320
Let me tell you.

250
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,060
A wife has to be subservient to her husband.

251
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:26,190
If you continue to make a fuss like this...

252
00:13:26,190 --> 00:13:27,120
What will you do?

253
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,340
What will you do?

254
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:30,350
I...

255
00:13:31,020 --> 00:13:32,180
Lian Shouren.

256
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:35,620
My family was rich back then.

257
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:37,950
My father advised me to marry you

258
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:39,700
and into this family of farmers,

259
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:40,500
because he thought

260
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:42,890
you were diligent in your studies

261
00:13:42,930 --> 00:13:45,330
and that you'll treat me well in the future.

262
00:13:46,210 --> 00:13:48,070
But ever since I've been with you,

263
00:13:48,350 --> 00:13:49,700
I just have an empty title

264
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,230
as a scholar's wife.

265
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:52,300
I haven't had

266
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:54,110
a single good day.

267
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:58,420
If my two sons

268
00:13:58,460 --> 00:13:59,870
didn't die early,

269
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:04,320
I wouldn't have to endure

270
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,100
this humiliation today.

271
00:14:06,310 --> 00:14:07,810
All right.

272
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:09,400
I feel bad

273
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:10,620
inside too.

274
00:14:10,830 --> 00:14:12,620
Shouyi and Shouxin both have sons.

275
00:14:12,620 --> 00:14:14,420
I'm the only one without a son.

276
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:15,830
How can the villagers

277
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:16,560
say about me?

278
00:14:17,260 --> 00:14:18,920
How can my friends

279
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:20,350
talk about it?

280
00:14:20,770 --> 00:14:22,530
If anything, it's your fault.

281
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,860
It's your womb's fault

282
00:14:23,860 --> 00:14:25,320
for being uncooperative.

283
00:14:38,580 --> 00:14:39,070
Man'er.

284
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:42,600
You were too impulsive today.

285
00:14:43,580 --> 00:14:45,580
About the matter of splitting from the family,

286
00:14:45,580 --> 00:14:47,180
don't ever mention it again.

287
00:14:48,230 --> 00:14:49,110
In a family,

288
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:51,340
tiny hurdles are inevitable.

289
00:14:53,710 --> 00:14:54,510
Tiny hurdles?

290
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,590
Uncle Shouren selling me off for widow burning

291
00:14:57,590 --> 00:14:58,520
is a tiny hurdle.

292
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,220
Asking my mother for the child

293
00:15:00,220 --> 00:15:00,980
she has been pregnant with for ten months

